outline.text: Hard swings - roll 2 die, max swings in time with working weight
Easy CnP or just MP 2 rungs lower than heavy day
Easy snatches, 2 die and 50-60% max with snatch test weight
Do whatever but take it easy
CnP ladders, 1 rung lower than heavy day
Moderate swings - 2 die, 70-80% effort with working weight
You may do any one, two, or all three of the following options
5 x 5 loaded cleans alternated with 5 x 1 get-ups with KB heavier than CnP ladders. Rest for a few minutes between sets
Do 2–3 sets of 5–10 swings and/or 2–3 sets of 1–10 snatches with a kettlebell heavier than the one you are doing timed sets with
Do whatever you want and take it easy.

No need to overcomplicate early on, keep it simple and follow structured progressions outlined. Once you've reached "simple standard", or are getting near to it and bored, we'll write the next program. Importance of learning the swing, and "bang-for-buck" of TGU cannot be stressed enough. You'll reach the standard for swings likely very quickly, TGUs might take a little longer.
Only session for now

Complete each progression as you achieve it. A progression is "complete" when you finish the sets in a timely period, without and breakdown of form.
If one progression is ridiculously easy, feel free to skip and add in an extra set etc. End goal is the "standard" at the end
Very straight forward progression. Keep rests between sets short without compromising form, some progressions are timed

Always start with bodyweight warmup*, a couple a side. Place a shoe on your closed fist and balance it overhead to practice the movement. Plenty of decent YT vids for direction. Look at StrongFirst - good up to date info
Not a progression per se, but worth practicing to begin with - less important as you become more accustomed to the move

outline.text: 3/3 roll to elbow (first stage of TGU, from floor to leaning on elbow)
outline._note: Once you can do 1 a side, you'll progress quickly

outline.text: 5/5 tall sit (up to elbow, then push through to tall-sit position, can explain separately)

outline._note: might require intermediate stages, but in my experience roll to elbow and tall-sit were the most challenging to start
